This paper deals with the problem of finding equilibria in multiplayer concurrent games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also proposes an algorithm for computing equilibria, which involves a transformation from multiplayer games to two-player games, and uses multidimensional mean-payoff games, which are topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of the decision problem for the existence of robust equilibria, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and systems and control (cs.SY). Overall, the paper is likely to be classified under cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.LG, and cs.SY, in decreasing order of likelihood.
